headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 15 points and 12 assists to lead the Denver Nuggets past Philadelphia 115-103 on Saturday, beating a 76ers team that had only seven available players because of injuries and COVID-19 protocols.
headlines.shortLinkText: Denver tops short-handed 76ers hit with virus, injuries

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball became the youngest player in NBA history to record a triple-double with 22 points, 12 rebounds and 11 assists, and the Charlotte Hornets beat the Atlanta Hawks 113-105 on Saturday night for their straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaMelo Ball becomes youngest NBA player with triple-double

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges scored a career-high 34 points and Devin Booker added 25, leading the Phoenix Suns to a 125-117 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges, Booker help Suns break through with win at Indiana

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored a career-high 31 points and Jimmy Butler nearly had a triple-double with 26 points, 10 rebounds and nine assists as the Miami Heat beat the short-handed Washington Wizards 128-124 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro's  31 points lead Heat over short-handed Wizards

headlines.description: — Khris Middleton scored 27 points and the Milwaukee Bucks withstood the absence of two-time reigning MVP Giannis Antetokounmpo to beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 100-90 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks beat Cavaliers 100-90 without injured Antetokounmpo

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Tim Hardaway Jr. scored a season-high 36 points, Trey Burke did the same with 29 and Luka Doncic had another triple-double as the short-handed Dallas Mavericks beat the Orlando Magic 112-98 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hardaway, Burke lead short-handed Mavs past Magic 112-98

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 37 points, making six 3-pointers, and the Portland Trail Blazers coasted to a 125-99 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum scores 37 as Trail Blazers rout Kings 125-99
